I"<p>A study explored the effectiveness of exercise programmes for treating depression in young people. They compared the results of a 3 times per week exercise regime with a stretching regime that lasted for 12 weeks.</p>

<p><strong>By the end of the study:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>86% of the exercise group and 50% of thee stretching group had fully recovered from their depressive symptoms.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The study followed up with participants a year later and found that the effect was maintained.</p>
  </li>
</ul>
